{"question":{"question_text":"Who will win the Tour de France 2025?","resolution_criteria":"This question will resolve as the cyclist who is officially recognized as the winner of the classement général, or overall winner, in the Tour de France 2025, based on results published on the Tour de France website or other credible sources.","fine_print":"If a cyclist not named in any option is the winner, the question will resolve as Other.

In the near-impossible event of a tie after all of the Tour de France's tiebreakers and no single winner of the general classification is declared, this question will be annulled.","background_information":"The Tour de France is an annual men's multiple stage bicycle race held primarily in France. It is the most prestigious bicycle race in the world. Its 112th edition will start in Lille, France, on July 5, 2025, and end on the Champs-Élysées in Paris on July 27, 2025.

Tadej Pogačar, possibly the most gifted cyclist of all time, is favored to win this year's Tour. He has previously won the race in 2020, 2021, and 2024. However, his main rival, Jonas Vingegaard, is exceptionally strong, and the Tour is notoriously dangerous; upsets and disaster are frequent.","expected_resolution_date":"2025-07-28T15:11:00Z","question_type":"multiple_choice","options":["Tadej Pogačar","Jonas Vingegaard","Remco Evenepoel","Primož Roglič","João Almeida","Juan Ayuso","Other"],"open_upper_bound":null,"open_lower_bound":null,"max_value":null,"min_value":null}}
